  "text": "In this study, multisensory integration was virtually abolished in younger adults when they directed attention selectively to vision or hearing, replicating previous findings [CITATION_1] . As hypothesized, older adults exhibited increased multisensory integration relative to younger adults in all attentional conditions. However, in contrast to our hypothesis, older adults evidenced successful instantiation of modality-specific attention. Integration was reduced under conditions of selective attention to vision or hearing relative to divided attention, and no attention cue Â group interactions were observed, suggesting that although older adults integrated more than younger adults, they showed a proportional reduction in integration because of modality-specific attention.",
